      <abstract>
        <p>British Airways reports its worst annual results since it was privatized in 1987, losing 244 million pounds, or $361 million, last year; pretax profit fell to 5 million pounds, down 97 percent, from 225 million pounds a year ago (S)</p>
      </abstract>
