    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Europe's largest airline, British Airways, reported its worst annual results since it was privatized in 1987, losing $:244 million, or $361 million, last year. The airline said its pretax profit fell to $:5 million, down 97 percent, from $:225 million a year ago. British Airways decided to retain its dividend at 17.9 pence.</p>
        <p>Andrew Ross Sorkin</p>
